Youths smash windows in Geneva anti - police demo . Some 150 youths protesting against alleged police violence smashed shop windows and damaged cars as they marched through central Geneva on Saturday . The youths , who told reporters they were part of a Europe - wide movement , also looted goods from a supermarket and stopped trolleybuses by pulling their electric cables off overhead wires , eyewitnesses said . Police said several of the demonstrators were detained , but the protest broke up after an hour . Such violence is rare in the Swiss international city . 
